Let‚Äôs explore ‚Äútoken ne‚Ä¶

4/ dApps & networks are just the light, transient interfaces that enable creation and recombination ad infinitum

the metaverse itself is the killer app

3/ what we're actually witnessing is a cambrian explosion of permanent, interoperable assets and their creators

code, text, jpegs, .wav, etc. all exist in this primordial digital soup with full provenance and computability

2/ web3 is not about the apps or gated networks that "own" assets or people (like we're used to)

it's about the assets, and it's about the people
1/ the most interesting thing about the web3 conversation is that it has yet to escape the closed world paradigm of "apps" and "networks"
